* Use getopts or getopt for parsing command-line arguments
* Add i386 support, currently we only support x86_64 arch.
* Script must be executable only as root. If not, throw a warning to stdout and exit 1.
* mkefi script should be executable with relatively directory iso path arguments.
* Script should exit immediately when executed via non-argument instead trying to mount something to somewhere.
* It'd be nice, If grub boot entry names are also configurable.
